        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/37b82b77d83d9db3e5b2784f2080dc3c?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 40248,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 116614,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/116614/mellamokb",
                "reputation": 56858,
                "display_name": "mellamokb",
                "accept_rate": 92
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 6,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1359763825,
            "creation_date": 1359763825,
            "body": "<p>Any Java class that you run directly must have a <code>main<\/code> method, which is the entry point, i.e., where the program starts when you execute the code.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public static void main(String args[])\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Just rename your method <code>contar()<\/code> to <code>main(String args[])<\/code> and it should work.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 14657162,
            "question_id": 14657147
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/wdzwu.png?s=256",
