            "last_activity_date": 1359998092,
            "creation_date": 1359764416,
            "body": "<p>Alternate to @mellamokb Answer <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public class Caneirinho{\n\n public static void contar(){\n   int i = 1;\n   String a = \" Carneirinho\",\n     b = \" pulando a cerca.\",\n     c = \"s\";\n\n   for(i=1; i&lt;=100; i++){\n     if(i==1){\n       System.out.println( i + a + b );\n      } else {     \n        System.out.println( i + a + c + b ); \n        Thread.sleep(1000);  // thread wais for 1 sec ie 1000 milisecond    \n      }     \n    }\n  }\n\npublic static void main(String[] args){\n   contar(); // call contar() from main method\n}\n\n}//Carneirinho\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 14657235,
            "question_id": 14657147,
            "last_edit_date": 1359998092
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/4b3f8f3525c4e7c41285dff7a3204098?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 1825514,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1658435,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1658435/user1658435",
                "reputation": 574,
                "display_name": "user1658435",
                "accept_rate": 90
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1359767490,
            "creation_date": 1359767490,
            "body": "<p>If you write a java program, it can have a number of classes but for all the classes to run we should have a main class which is used to implement the classes which we defined. You created a class without main in it. The program will start its execution from main. <\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 14657569,
